        document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', function () {
            const toggleButton = document.getElementById('toggleDetails');
            const filterButton = document.getElementById('filterMessages');
            const filterOverlay = document.getElementById('filterOverlay');
            const applyFilterButton = document.getElementById('applyFilter');
            const selectAllButton = document.getElementById('selectAll');
            const selectNoneButton = document.getElementById('selectNone');

            // Toggle details functionality
            function updateToggleButton() {
                const allDetails = document.querySelectorAll('details.collapsible-details');
                const openCount = document.querySelectorAll('details[open].collapsible-details').length;
                const totalCount = allDetails.length;

                if (totalCount === 0) {
                    toggleButton.style.display = 'none';
                    return;
                }

                // If more than half are open, show "close all" state, otherwise show "open all"
                const mostlyOpen = openCount > totalCount / 2;
                toggleButton.textContent = mostlyOpen ? '📦' : '🗃️';
                toggleButton.title = mostlyOpen ? 'Close all details' : 'Open all details';
            }

            function toggleAllDetails() {
                const allDetails = document.querySelectorAll('details.collapsible-details');
                const openCount = document.querySelectorAll('details[open].collapsible-details').length;
                const shouldOpen = openCount <= allDetails.length / 2;

                allDetails.forEach(details => {
                    if (shouldOpen) {
                        details.setAttribute('open', '');
                    } else {
                        details.removeAttribute('open');
                    }
                });

                updateToggleButton();
            }

            toggleButton.addEventListener('click', toggleAllDetails);

            // Filter functionality
            const messageTypes = ['user', 'assistant', 'system', 'tool_use', 'tool_result', 'thinking', 'image'];
            
            function showFilterModal() {
                filterOverlay.style.display = 'flex';
                document.body.style.overflow = 'hidden';
            }

            function hideFilterModal() {
                filterOverlay.style.display = 'none';
                document.body.style.overflow = 'auto';
            }

            function selectAllTypes() {
                messageTypes.forEach(type => {
                    const checkbox = document.getElementById(`filter-${type}`);
                    if (checkbox) checkbox.checked = true;
                });
            }

            function selectNoTypes() {
                messageTypes.forEach(type => {
                    const checkbox = document.getElementById(`filter-${type}`);
                    if (checkbox) checkbox.checked = false;
                });
            }

            function applyFilter() {
                const selectedTypes = messageTypes.filter(type => {
                    const checkbox = document.getElementById(`filter-${type}`);
                    return checkbox && checkbox.checked;
                });

                // Show/hide messages based on selected types
                const allMessages = document.querySelectorAll('.message:not(.session-header)');
                allMessages.forEach(message => {
                    const shouldShow = selectedTypes.some(type => message.classList.contains(type));
                    if (shouldShow) {
                        message.classList.remove('filtered-hidden');
                    } else {
                        message.classList.add('filtered-hidden');
                    }
                });

                // Update filter button appearance to indicate active filtering
                const allTypesSelected = selectedTypes.length === messageTypes.length;
                filterButton.style.backgroundColor = allTypesSelected ? '#e8f4fd66' : '#fff3cd66';
                filterButton.title = allTypesSelected ? 'Filter messages' : 'Filter messages (active)';

                hideFilterModal();
            }

            // Event listeners
            filterButton.addEventListener('click', showFilterModal);
            selectAllButton.addEventListener('click', selectAllTypes);
            selectNoneButton.addEventListener('click', selectNoTypes);
            applyFilterButton.addEventListener('click', applyFilter);

            // Close modal when clicking outside
            filterOverlay.addEventListener('click', function(e) {
                if (e.target === filterOverlay) {
                    hideFilterModal();
                }
            });

            // Close modal with Escape key
            document.addEventListener('keydown', function(e) {
                if (e.key === 'Escape' && filterOverlay.style.display === 'flex') {
                    hideFilterModal();
                }
            });

            // Make filter options clickable
            messageTypes.forEach(type => {
                const option = document.querySelector(`label[for="filter-${type}"]`);
                if (option) {
                    option.addEventListener('click', function(e) {
                        e.preventDefault();
                        const checkbox = document.getElementById(`filter-${type}`);
                        if (checkbox) {
                            checkbox.checked = !checkbox.checked;
                        }
                    });
                }
            });

            // Initialize button state
            updateToggleButton();
        });
    </script>

content.text:
Perfect! I've redesigned the toolbar layout using CSS Grid for much better control over the layout. Here's what I've improved:

## ✅ New Grid Layout Structure

**📐 CSS Grid**: Three-column layout with `grid-template-columns: auto 1fr auto`
**🏷️ Fixed Label**: "Filter:" stays in left column with fixed width
**🎛️ Flexible Middle**: Filter toggle buttons wrap naturally in the center column
**⚙️ Fixed Actions**: "All", "None", "✕" buttons stay in right column with fixed width

## Layout Benefits

### Column Structure
1. **Left Column (`auto`)**: "Filter:" label with fixed width
2. **Middle Column (`1fr`)**: Flexible space for filter toggles with proper wrapping
3. **Right Column (`auto`)**: Action buttons with fixed width

### Improved Wrapping
- **Natural Flow**: Filter buttons wrap to multiple lines cleanly in the center
- **Consistent Alignment**: All elements stay vertically centered
- **No Awkward Breaks**: Label and actions never break inappropriately
- **Responsive**: Layout adapts gracefully to different screen sizes

### Visual Improvements
- **Better Spacing**: 16px gap between grid columns
- **Centered Content**: All sections use `align-items: center`
- **Clean Wrapping**: Filter toggles use `justify-content: center` when wrapping
- **No Layout Shifts**: Fixed-width side columns prevent jumping

The toolbar now maintains a professional, organized appearance even when filter buttons wrap to multiple lines, with the label and action buttons always staying in their proper positions!
